  "name": "Indus CISI: Anchored Decipherment — 5 Anchor Readings",
  "description": "Extended anchored decipherment with 5 structurally motivated readings. Anchors: P385→'n' (genitive suffix, T=0.83, n=35); P324→'k' (INITIAL, n=99, I=0.78); P122→'a' (pure MEDIAL n=76, M=1.00, most frequent medial — acts as vowel carrier for the stem before genitive); P086→'m' (INITIAL n=35, I=0.54 — second most common initial after P324, likely 'man', 'min', 'mul' type word-initial); P060→'i' (pure MEDIAL n=20, M=0.95 — common inner vowel). The pattern P324(k)+...+P122(a)+P385(n) = 'k...an' → Dravidian word in genitive. E.g. P324+P122+P385 = 'kan' = 'eye' (Tamil kan+in genitive). GPU: ocp_weight=0.0, n_seeds=8, max_iter=12000.",
